@EndNode

@Node ConfigFiles "ConfigFiles"

  Config Files
  ============

    <filename>.CFG (e.g if door was renamed to moo.hbbs then cfg file
    -------------- would be moo.cfg in the same directory as moo.hbbs

      @{"AccessLevel" link CFG_AccessLevel} - Access Level assigned to new users
      @{"ConfNum    " link CFG_ConfNum    } - Conference Number to join
      @{"TimeAllowed" link CFG_TimeAllowed} - Amount of time a new user is allowed

@EndNode

@Node CFG_AccessLevel "AccessLevel"

  AccessLevel=<number>

    E.G.

    AccessLevel=10

    No Default, required

    This is the access level that is given to a new user when they join the
    system

    This access level must be defined in the "HBBS:Access/Levels/Level_List"
    file.

@EndNode

@Node CFG_ConfNum "ConfNum"

  ConfNum=<number>

    E.G.

    ConfNum=4

    No Default, required, must be a valid conference number.

    The new user will join this conference when they first login to the BBS

    Note, this is the actual conference number, not the number that would be
    seen by this user if they used the JoinConference door from the BBS
    prompt.

@EndNode

@Node CFG_TimeAllowed "TimeAllowed"

  TimeAllowed=<number>

    E.G.

    TimeAllowed=20

    No Default, required

    This specifies the amout of time (in mins) that the user is allowed per
    day by default, until the sysop changes their account details.

@EndNode

